<HEADLINE> Greece Sends Medical Aid to Quake-Hit Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Greece today sent 20 tons of medical
supplies to Iran to help the victims of the devastating earthquake
which hit eastern Iran last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A Greek Air Force C-130 transport plane, carrying the medical
supplies, left for the region today and the government said a
second shipment would follow in the next few days. Greece has also
offered to send a team of three surgeons.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that more than 2,000 poeple were killed and 3,712
injured in the earthquake which measured 7.1 on the Richter
scale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
