<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, May 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Three Israeli soldiers and two Hezbollah gunmen
were killed Thursday night during fierce clashes in South
Lebanon, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
AMSTERDAM -- Local and regional leaders and representatives in
the European Union (EU) today started discussions on how the
regions and cities could better contribute to the European
integration.
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- A more punitive measure is likely to be taken by the
International Labor Organization (ILO) against Nigeria over its
continued poor human rights record, the Guardian reported today.
</P>
<P>
HAVANA -- After a road accident two months ago that strained
Cuban-Spanish relations, Cuba welcomes a planned visit by Spanish
King Juan Carlos I and Queen Dona Sofia, the Foreign Ministry said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) have agreed to jointly search for remains
of American servicemen missing in the Korean War, the Pentagon
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
WELLINGTON -- Tension in the New Zealand  parliament has
heightened between the opposition and Deputy Prime Minister
Winston Peters over the issue of he allegedly assaulting a
National backbencher more than two months ago.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said here
Thursday that Moscow's opposition to NATO's eastward expansion was
unchanged. 
</P>
