<HEADLINE> Yemen Beats Cambodia 7-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANA, Yemen, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Omar Abdul Rahman staged a
scoring exhibition with five goals to his credit to lead host
Yeman to a 7-0 victory over Cambodia in a World Cup Asian Zone
Group 5 qualifier here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The other two goals of the match were scored by Munir Shaef and
Diab Bashafaei.
</P>
<P>
Yeman dominated the match in front of 30,000 home spectators.
The victory gave the Yemeni team 7 points, two more than Indonesia
and four more than Asian Games champion Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia has drawn only one of its four matches and has scored
only one goal but conceded 17 goals.
</P>
<P>
Yemen will play against Indonesia on June while Uzbekistan will
take on Cambodia on May 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
