<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Life Insurance Congress Set for HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Fourth Asia-Pacific Life
Insurance Congress (APLIC) has been slated for August 21-24 in
Hong Kong, organizers announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The event, to take place at the Hong Kong Coliseum, is expected
to attract some 10,000 delegates from 11 Asian and Pacific
countries and regions. And some 50 speakers from 14 countries
including the United States, Japan, Singapore, Thailand and
Malaysia have also confirmed their participation.
</P>
<P>
Located at the very heart of the region, Hong Kong is widely
recognized as the economic and business hub of Asia. The handover
later this year has definitely drawn world attention to Hong Kong
and it signifies a new era in Hong Kong and a golden year to
explore new opportunities in all industries, according to the
organizers.
</P>
<P>
"The timely congress, entitled 'New Horizon,' will surely mark
the beginning of a new era in the history of Hong Kong, China as
well as the Asian and Pacific region," said Congress Chairman Tony
Mak.
</P>
<P>
"The Life Underwriters Association of Hong Kong is proud to be
the organizer of this coming APLIC," he added.
</P>
<P>
Discussions and talks at the congress will cover information
from personnel training to corporate management, in such areas as
sales ideas, customer service, personnel development, agency
management, self motivation and technical knowledge.
</P>
<P>
APLIC is a biyearly event and the three previous meetings were
held in Singapore, Malaysia and Australia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
