<HEADLINE> Commonwealth to Discuss Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 education ministers from
all commonwealth countries will gather togather in Gaborone, capital
of Botswana, in July to discuss education, according to the Post
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will discuss how to harness appropriate
technology to develop education, the local newspaper quoted the
Botswana Gazette as saying.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition will be run parallel to the meeting and students
looking for career guidance will have an opportunity to go through up
to 100 stands for academic institutions.
</P>
<P>
Educationists will also be able to catch up on the latest
educational methods and the exhibitors will showcase a number of
interactive case studies highlighting best practices in the rapidly
expanding educational markets through the Commonwealth.
</P>
<P>
Business people who deal in educational products will also get a
chance to sell their products.  enditem



