<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zairian President Mobutu Leaves His Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, Zaire May 16 (Xinhua) _ Zairian President Mobutu Sese
Seko has given up running the government and left the capital
today, his information minister Kin-Kiey said today.
</P>
<P>
The minister said to reporters that Mobutu would retain the
title of president. It appeared, however, that Mobutu was
retreating from any significant role in Zaire as rebels close in
on the capital, Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that Mobutu had "ceased all intervention in
the conduct of affairs of state. He reigns but does not govern."
</P>
<P>
Mobutu's departure followed reports that his three top generals
told him they could not and would not defend the capital.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu slipped out of the capital so quietly today that many
residents did not know he was gone.
</P>
<P>
The capital was calm, with markets, shops and restaurants open
and the streets filled with residents. But truckloads of
machine-gun toting soldiers were out in force today along the road
to the airport.
</P>
<P>
A Western diplomat, speaking on condition of anonymity, said
there was a strong chance that Mobutu would flee the country
today. French TV TF1 said Mobutu was going to Morocco, then on to
France, where he has a villa on the Riviera. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
