<HEADLINE> Zambia to Restructure Medical Stores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Medical stores, the only supplier of
essential drugs and medicines in Zambia, will be restructured soon,
Zambia daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Managing Director Oliver Hazemba as saying the company
will undergo a full restructuring process of all its operations to
transform it into a more economically viable business.
</P>
<P>
The company will spend 1.5 billion Kwacha (about 1.2 million
US dollars) on down sizing the excess workforce and another 450,000
dollars on improving the operational system.
</P>
<P>
The company will only retain half the current 750 employees in the
retrenchment exercise to be begun next week and bring it even further
down in the future, said the director.
</P>
<P>
Major areas to be restructured include the storage facility,
distribution and transport and the procurement system. enditem

