<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Historical Photo Album to Be Published in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale documentary photo
album entitled "Hong Kong" is soon to be published here, it was
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The album will be jointly published by the Beijing-based Xinhua
News Agency and the Hong Kong-based Sino United Publishing
(Holdings) Ltd. and it is to be distributed by the Commercial
Press (Hong Kong) Ltd.
</P>
<P>
With more than 600 photos, the album consists of three parts --
"Historical Vicissitudes" which portrays Hong Kong's past,
"Economic Takeoff" which presents the current days and "The
Homeward Road" which helps the readers learn of the events leading
to Hong Kong's handover.
</P>
<P>
"A history never to forget and an album really worthy to keep,"
Steven Luk, director of Sino United Publishing (Holdings) Ltd.,
said of the album.
</P>
<P>
China will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on
July 1, 1997, and the album "is a record of such a transition," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The album will be published in three editions -- souvenir,
deluxe and hard-bound.  
</P>
</TEXT>
