<HEADLINE> UN Council Okays Increase of UN Police in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security Council on
Friday approved an increase in strength of U.N. International
Police Task Force in Bosnia by 120 police personnel.
</P>
<P>
In a unanimously adopted resolution, the council urged member
states to provide qualified police monitors and other forms of
assistance and support to the force.
</P>
<P>
The council took the move at the suggestion of U.N.
Secretary-General Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
He said a substantial number of police experts were needed on
human rights investigation, monitoring of the local police,
strengthening of police training, police restructuring and the
development of guidelines for democratic policing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
