<HEADLINE> Tunisia Desires Closer Ties with Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Tunisian President Zine Al-Abidine
Bin-Ali said here today that he attributes great importance to the
cooperative relations between his country and Libya.
</P>
<P>
The president made this clear during a meeting with Prime
minister Hamed Al-karoui, who was set to open talks with his
Libyan counterpart in Jerba island, east Tunisia, later today,
according to Tunisia-Africa News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The talks would focus on closer bilateral cooperation between
the two countries, a desire shared by President Bin-Ali and his
Libyan counterpart Colonel Moammar Gaddafi.
</P>
<P>
Bin Ali reiterated that both countries and peoples would
benefit from overall cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that it was necessary to follow up the
implementation of joint development projects and to fully tap the
potentials of both sides. 
</P>
