<HEADLINE> China's Hubei Economic Delegation Visits Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of Commerce
and Industry Kasahun Ayele today praised the long existing
Sino-Ethiopian friendship and cooperation, saying
that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to Ethiopia last year
has pushed the friendly relations between the two countries to a new stage.
</P>
<P>
Kasahun made the remarks when he met the visiting
China's Hubei economic delegation led by provincial Governor
Jiang Zhuping.
</P>
<P>
Kasahun said, Ethiopia which is an important country in
Africa, needs Chinese investment and technology. China has
experience in developing small-scale industry, Ethiopia wants to
learn from China's experience.
</P>
<P>
The eight member delegation arrived last night for a three-day
visit here at the invitation of Addis Ababa regional
administration.
</P>
<P>
The Hubei delegation this morning held talks with Addis Ababa
regional delegation led by the Addis Ababa regional President Ali
Abdo. both sides expressed their wish to develop economic
relations.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Vice-Minister of Planning and Economic Cooperation
Mulato Teshome met the Chinese Hubei delegation.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is the first step of the Hubei delegation's
four-nation tour which will take the delegation to Rwanda,
Cameroun and Israel. 
</P>
