<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 18:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Bombards Hezbollah Bases in Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Israeli warplanes carried out today
some 15 rounds of bombing at guerrilla positions of the
pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God, in south Lebanon today.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Israeli artillery fired more than 400 shells
at the same targets.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in south Lebanon reported that the Israeli
warplanes unleashed one round of bombing in every 20 minutes
since 8:00 a.m. local time (05:00 GMT) and until the noon at
targets on the hill of Telal Al-Dhahr in Western Beqaa, some 85
kilometers southeast of Beirut.
</P>
<P>
The warplanes launched a dozen of air-to-surface missiles and
shot bursts of machinegun fires in the air strikes, the anonymous
sources reported, noting that no casualties were caused.
</P>
<P>
In a separate raid, Israeli helicopters rocketed a Lebanese
army checkpoint on the edge of the Israeli self-proclaimed
"security zone," the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah guerrillas and Lebanese army units in Western Beqaa
fired with anti-air weapons at the Israeli warplanes, but missed
the targets.
</P>
<P>
Israeli artillery fired more than 50 shells at areas around
the attacked guerrilla positions in the morning.
</P>
<P>
At 1:00 p.m. (10:00 a.m. GMT), the Israeli forces in the border
strip resumed the bombardments and fired more 120mm and 150mm
shells.
</P>
<P>
Sources in the U.N. peacekeeping forces operating in south
Lebanon reported that more than 400 artillery shells were fired at
Western Beqaa today.
</P>
<P>
The air raids came hours after a violent clash between
Hezbollah fighters and Israeli commandos near Telal Al-Dhahr
overnight.
</P>
<P>
Israeli army admitted that in the fighting, which lasted from
9:00 p.m. (18:00 GMT) until 0:10 a.m. (21:10 GMT), three Israeli
soldiers were killed and seven others wounded, the worst loss for
the 1,000-strong Israeli forces in a single clash since this year.
</P>
<P>
General Amiran Levine, commander of Israel's northern military
area, said the clash erupted when the Israeli commandos were
fulfilling a routine mission inside the buffer zone.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the exchange of fire with the guerrillas in a
short distance, one Israeli soldier was killed and two others were
wounded, and the commandos sustained additional casualties during
evacuation efforts.
</P>
<P>
In Beirut, Hezbollah said that its fighters ambushed the
Israeli force attempting to infiltrate out of the
Israeli-occupied border strip.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said two guerrillas were killed, but the
Shiite Muslim organization denied any casualties among its
fighters.
</P>
<P>
The clash has brought the Israeli casualties to nine killed and
40 injured in south Lebanon since this year. Last year, 27 Israeli
soldiers were killed in clashes with Hezbollah guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah spearheads a guerrilla warfare in south Lebanon in a
bid to drive the Israeli forces out of the 1,100-square-kilometer
buffer zone, which the Jewish state established in 1985.
</P>
<P>
A senior Israeli official has said that Iran had supplied
large quantities of weapons to Hezbollah during the first quarter
of this year, including some much more sophisticated than those
used by Hezbollah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
