<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays $370 Million Loans for Projects in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of three loans totaling 370 million U.S. dollars for
projects in Argentina and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Argentina's Second Maternal and Child Health and Nutrition
Project will be supported by a 100 million dollar loan from the
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The project will help expand and refurbish health facilities
and laboratories, to increase maternal and prenatal health care
services and pediatric services for children under six years old
and to help transform existing child care centers into early
childhood development centers.
</P>
<P>
The project will also provide training and technical assistance
to decentralize and strengthen government social services.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of equivalent to 200 million dollars is earmarked
for Argentina's Urban Transport Project in Buenos Aires, capital
of the country.
</P>
<P>
The project will finance civil works and equipment to upgrade
public transport services, including road and rail systems,
transport safety and environmental conditions.
</P>
<P>
The project will also provide technical assistance and
supervision to enhance the transport system in the Buenos Aires
metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
The Bank also approved a 70 million dollar loan for Brazil Rio
Grande do Sul State Highway Management Project.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to help finance the rebuilding,
repaving, and maintenance of roads, related studies, engineering
designs and works supervisions and technical assistance,
equipment, software and training for the country's state Road
Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
