<HEADLINE> New Date for Liberia's Polls Due to Be Fixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 16 (Xinhua) -- West African Leaders are scheduled
to meet in Abuja, capital of Nigeria, next week to review the
implementation of the ongoing peace plan for Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The one-day summit of the Committee of Nine on Liberia of the
Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) is expected to
decide a new date for the election and the swearing-in of a new
government as widely anticipated.
</P>
<P>
