which is scheduled for next Wednesday and also expected to agree
on modalities for providing the logistics for the elections, the
official news agency added.
</P>
<P>
Under the ECOWAS-brokered AbujaA peace plan signed last
August, Liberia's legislative and presidential elections are
scheduled for May 30, with the new government to swear-in on June
15.
</P>
<P>
However, some people complained about the insecurity in some
areas of the country, the absence of logistics, voter education
program, and the domination of the government by appointees of
former warlords.
</P>
<P>
According to the Nigeria News Agency, a delegation, representing
the political interests in Liberia, is already in Nigeria for
preparatory talks with Nigerian head of state General Sani
Abacha, who is the Chairman of ECOWAS. 
