<HEADLINE> Switzerland Finances Tanzania's Road, Dairy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland will allocate
10.8 billion T. Shillings (about 18 million U.S. Dollars) to
Tanzania for Morogoro Roads Support Project (MRSP) and the
development of dairy farming in the Iringa and Mbeya regions.
</P>
<P>
Two agreements concerned were signed here today by Swiss
Ambassador to Tanzania Lise Favre and Tanzanian Deputy Principal
Secretary Gray Ngonja.
</P>
<P>
The move aims at the maintanence and rehabilitation of the
road network in the Morogoro region under MRSP, estimated to cost
13.1 billion T.Shs, with 9.3 billion of them from Switzerland and
3.8 billion from the Tanzanian government.
</P>
<P>
A joint press release said that the project will generally
contribute to the objectives of the national Integrated Roads
Project (IRP).
</P>
<P>
"Its goal is to increase agricultural production in the region
through removal of transport constraints," said the press
release.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Swiss government, through the Southern
Highlands Dairy Development Project (SHDDP), will allocate 1.5
billion T. Shs. to improve nutrition of the people and dairy
farmers' income in the Iringa and Mbeya regions. 
</P>
