<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNEP to Hold Meeting on Environment, Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 350 leading bankers and
financial experts from around the world will attend a UN meeting
next Thursday and Friday to consider new strategies for
investments and loans for environmental initiatives.
</P>
<P>
The third round-table meeting on finance and environment,
organized by the United Nations Environment Program (UNEP), will
explore the challenges the financial services sector faces in
translating corporate environmental information into financially
relevant terms of use by financial analysts.
</P>
<P>
In a discussion of "Environmental opportunities and Issues in
Private Finance," the meeting, to be held on the campus of
Columbia University, will look at three industries, namely energy,
water and forestry, which are currently receiving considerable
attention from both the financial and environmental communities.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the meeting also include topics on
environmental disclosures and reporting, opportunities for green
investment and innovative policy initiatives for various
industry sectors and challenges in relating environmental
performance to financial performance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
