<HEADLINE> S.Africa, Norway Reaffirm Cooperation, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The South African government
and the Norwegian government have reaffirmed their commitment to
going ahead with a cooperation and development agreement signed
two years ago, a local press report said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued in Pretoria by the Foreign Affairs
Ministry, the Norwegian government will continue its support of some
18 million U.S.Dollars until 1999.
</P>
<P>
Under the current cooperation agreement, Norway has committed
itself to broaden its support in line with the Reconstruction and
Development Program of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The agreement aims to consolidate democracy and improve
socio-economic development by focusing on human rights, primary
education, housing, environmental affairs and small-scale
industry, said the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
