<HEADLINE> HK Defeat USA in Pacific Rim Rugby Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Hong Kong scored their
second victory in the on-going Pacific Rim Rugby Championship by
trouncing the United States 46-9 in the tournament's third match
here today.
</P>
<P>
In the championship's opening match here on May 3, Hong Kong
trounced Japan 42-20.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Hong Kong, third finishers at last year's championship,
led the Americans, runners-up in 1996, 22-9 in the first half
today. The Hong Kong players made it three tries, two conversions
and one penalty.
</P>
<P>
Relying much on their quick-footed wings, Hong Kong went on
with their penetrating play in the second half. They scored three
 more tries and, with three conversions and one penalty, widened
the gap to 37 points at the end of the match. The Americans
failed to collect any single point in the second half.
</P>
<P>
In the tournament's second match on May 10 in Vancouver, hosts
and last year's champions Canada beat the United States 53-14.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong led the team standings with eight points from two
straight wins, followed by Canada with four points from one
victory, and the United States with two from two defeats and Japan
on a sole point.
</P>
<P>
The tournament has adopted a single round-robin system, with a
total of 10 matches on the schedule.
</P>
<P>
The next match of the tournament will be held in Japan
tomorrow, with the hosts Japan playing Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
