<HEADLINE> China's Biggest Petrochemical Joint Venture Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The biggest petrochemical joint
venture in China became operational today in this port city in
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian West Pacific Petrochemical Company LTD. is jointly
run by several Chinese companies and the Total Company of
France. The project will involve an investment of some one billion
US dollars and have an annual crude oil refining capacity of five
million tons. The contract term will last to the year 2040. 
</P>
