<HEADLINE> Cipollini Wins Giro First Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Mario Cipollini of Italy won the
opening stage of the 80th Giro d'Italia cycling race at Venice on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini edged ahead after battling shoulder-to-shoulder with
Nicola Minali over the final meters.
</P>
<P>
Minali finished second, followed by his Italian compatriot
Endrio Leoni in the third place.
</P>
<P>
The stage victory is the ninth of the year for Cipollini. The
victory earned him a time deduction of 12 seconds with Minali
taking eight seconds off and Leoni four. 
</P>
</TEXT>
