<HEADLINE> Russia to Enhance Cooperation With United Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
said today his country will strengthen cooperation with the
United Nations and support the world body's reform.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan, he
also pledged that Russia would not fall into arrears on its UN
membership dues in future.
</P>
<P>
Russia was the United Nations' second largest debtor at the end
of 1996, with 300 million U.S. dollars owing, mainly for
peacekeeping. But it has announced a repayment plan. The U.S. is
the largest debtor.
</P>
<P>
Annan arrived here Wednesday for his first Russian trip. He
said his meeting with Yeltsin had been very beneficial and said
the two had discussed and exchanged ideas over issues relating to
NATO's expansion, chemical weapons and regional conflicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
