<HEADLINE> Defense Minister Urges Boost for Army Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Defense Minister Chi Haotian
today urged that the building of the People's Liberation Army be
strengthened in an all-round way in accordance with President
Jiang Zemin's instructions.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking at a meeting in this capital of east China's
Shandong Province to mark the 50th anniversary of the victory of a
battle against Kuomintang troops.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that political education is part of the fine tradition
of the Chinese army, and it should be carried forward in the new
situation.
</P>
<P>
He called on the troops to hearken to the instructions of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and the Central Military
Commission with Jiang Zemin at the core, and to firmly resist the
influence of decadent ideology and bad life styles.
</P>
<P>
He added that, in light of rapid advances being made in
weaponry, officers and men should learn how to use high-technology
equipment, and thus be ready to win a modern war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
