<HEADLINE> Kurds in Germany Protest over Turkish Drive in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 2,000 Kurds today protested
outside the Turkish consulate in the southwestern German city of
Stuttgart against the recent Turkish military operation in
northern Iraq, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
They called on Germany and the European Union to exert pressure
on the Turkish government to end the assault against the guerillas
of the Turkish separatist Workers Party of Kurdistan (PKK), which
they said had mainly affected the civilian population in that
area.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish troops, of reportedly 25,000 to 50,000 soldiers and
backed by tanks and heavy artillery, crossed the border into
northern Iraq on Wednesday. According to Turkish authorities, at
least 87 "separatist terrorists" and a solider have been killed.
</P>
<P>
Baghdad has protested against the Turkish move, saying it
violated international law.  
</P>
</TEXT>
