<HEADLINE> Corretja Reaches Italian Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Alex Corretja of Spain beat Goran
Ivanisevic 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-4) to reach the final of the Italian
Open men's tennis tournament here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 10th-seeded Corretja played a steady match against
sixth-seeded Ivanisevic and won the two tiebreakers to claim the
match in two hours.
</P>
<P>
Corretja has already won a clay event in Estoril, Portugal. He
was also runner-up at Monte Carlo and Munich.
</P>
<P>
In the second semi-final match later on Saturday, Marcelo Rios
of Chile will play Alberto Berasategui of Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
