<HEADLINE> 35 Rebels Charged With Treason in Western Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Thirtyfive rebels of the Allied Democratic
Forces (ADF) have been accused at a court in western Ugandan city
of Mbarara on charge of treason, "The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The accused imposed a war against the state last November in
cooperation with others still at large, prosecutors said.
</P>
<P>
The ADF was then a rebel group which had bases in eastern
Zaire. It launched an invasion into western Uganda last November
and lost its main forces in the following battles with the
government troops last December and January.
</P>
<P>
The ADF had 1,200 fighters when it invaded into
western Uganda last November, but a recent report said its
fighters had decreased to 300 who were devided into some small
groups acting in the west. 
</P>
</TEXT>
