<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 33 Injured in Car Accidents in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Eight persons were killed and
33 others injured in car accidents that occured in Addis Ababa
during the past week, the Ethiopian police announced today.
</P>
<P>
In an announcement quoted by the Ethiopian News Agency, the
Addis Ababa Police Commission said 146 car accidents occured in
the capital during the stated period.
</P>
<P>
It further said, about 5,400 drivers were fined for violating
traffic regulations in the city during the same period. 
