<HEADLINE> Tongji University Celebrates 90th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Tongji University, located in this
east China metropolis and one of China's oldest modern
universities, celebrated the 90th anniversary of its founding
today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders, including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi and
Li Ruihuan, sent congratulatory inscriptions for the
celebration. They praised the school's remarkable contributions to
the country's modernization drive and encouraged it to cultivate
more professional talents for the cause of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Tongji University is a key comprehensive university jointly run
by the Shanghai municipal government and the State Education
Commission. More than 100,000 students have graduated from the
university since it was founded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
