<HEADLINE> Indonesia 45 Percent Chance to Win Sudriman Cup: Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian shuttlers
have a 45 percent chance to win the Sudirman Cup world mixed team
championship, Indonesian head coach Indra Gunawan said here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But he said Denmark could be the biggest obstacle his team has
to surmount in group matches.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese team is of course the strongest. But we are good
as well," Indra Gunawan told Xinhua. "To tell the truth, we have
45 percent and the Chinese have the other 55 percent chance."
</P>
<P>
He said men's singles world champion Heryanto Arbi shook off
his injuries and is now 100 percent fit while Joko Suprianto has
recovered from a thigh injury that he suffered in World Grand Prix
Finals in December.
</P>
<P>
Mia Audina, Olympic silver medalist and world number three in
women's singles and the country's "badminton queen" Susi Susanti
are also in good form, he said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia, which lost to China 1-4 in the 1995 Sudirman Cup
final, are in Group B of the top-flight Division 1 in the
preliminary stage along with Denmark and Sweden. China, South
Korea and England are in Group A.
</P>
<P>
Gunawan said he was most worried about the group meeting
against Denmark, especially the men's doubles match.
</P>
<P>
The newly formed Danish duo Jon Holst-Christensen and Michael
Sogaard have recently beaten Indonesia's Olympic gold medalists
Ricky Subagja and Rexy Mainaky.
</P>
<P>
They have also defeated Malaysia's Olympic silver medalists
Cheah Soon Kit and Yap Kim Hock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
