<HEADLINE> Mary Joe Fernandez Enters German Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Mary Joe Fernandez of the United
States beat second-seeded Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic to
enter the final of the German Open women's tennis tournament here
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It will be Fernandez's first final of the year. Fernandez, the
tenth-seeded player in the tournament, played steadily in the
match, beating her higher-seeded rival 6-3, 6-1 in one
hour and 16 minutes.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Fernandez also took revenge of Novotna who beat
her in last year's Atlanta Olympic Games. 
</P>
