<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLC Holds 7th Meeting in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) held its seventh plenary meeting in South China's Shenzhen
city today to do the first and second readings of five amendment
bills.
</P>
<P>
Presented by Michael Suen, secretary for policy coordination of
the HKSAR Chief Executive's Office, the bills include the Urban
Council (Amendment) Bill 1997, Regional Council (Amendment) Bill
1997, District Boards (Amendment) Bill 1997, Public Order
(Amendment) Bill 1997 and Societies (Amendment) Bill 1997.
</P>
<P>
On the bills concerning the Urban Council, Regional Council and
District Boards, Suen said that according to the related
decisions made by the Standing Committee of China's National
People's Congress (NPC), the last session of the Urban Council,
Regional Council and District Boards under the British Hong Kong
Authority shall stop functioning by July 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that the 24th meeting of the NPC Standing Committee
held on February 23 this year also ruled that the articles on the
election of the members of the councils and district boards in the
"Urban Council Ordinance," "Regional Council Ordinance" and
"District Board Ordinance" shall not be adopted as laws of the
HKSAR due to their contravening the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Since the first session of the Urban Council, Regional Council
and District Boards could not be formed through election before
July 1, 1997, it is necessary to set up the Provisional Urban
Council, Provisional Regional Council and Provisional District
Boards to operate in place of the Urban Council, Regional Council
and District Boards.
</P>
<P>
The first meetings of the members of the Provisional Urban
Council, Provisional Regional Council and Provisional Legislative
Council are to be held before July 7 this year and the tenure of
the councils and boards is limited to December 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
On the Public Order and Societies Bills, Suen said that PLC
members debated the two bills last Saturday and they expressed
their support for the fundamental principles underlying the
proposed amendments.
</P>
<P>
According to Suen, the principles include ensuring a proper
balance between civil liberties and social order, upholding the
Basic Law and the International Covenant on Civil and Political
Rights as they are applied to Hong Kong, and guarding against
interference by foreign political forces in local political
activities.
</P>
<P>
The meeting proceeded with the first and second readings of the
five bills and the debate on them was adjourned.
</P>
<P>
The meeting adopted the Report of the Working Group on
Administrative Matters.
</P>
<P>
A motion on increasing the standard rate under the
comprehensive social security assistance scheme for the elderly by
a PLC member was discussed and the debate on it was adjourned.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting the Fifth House Committee of the PLC
discussed means of public consultation, seating arrangement for
members at council meetings, and ceremonial and logistical
arrangements for July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, two bills committees were set up to study
the Urban Council Bill, Regional Council Bill and District Boards
Bill as well as Public Order Bill and Societies Bill.
</P>
<P>
The Bills Committee on National Flag and National Emblem Bill
and Regional Flag and Regional Emblem Bill also held a meeting to
discuss the two bills with representatives of the Chief
Executive's Office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
