<HEADLINE> Minor Earthquake Hits Eastern Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.3 on the
Richter scale hit Baxoi County in the eastern part of the Tibet
Autonomous Region at 19:18 (Beijing Time) Friday, according to the
China Seismological Observatories Network.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was located 30.5 degrees north latitude and 97.1
degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
However, due to difficulties in communication with the remote
area where the quake occurred there is no information on
casualties so far.  
</P>
