<HEADLINE> French President Visits Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 17 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
met here today with Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome to Chirac, Xu said that Shanghai,
China's largest industrial city, is keen on increasing exchanges
and cooperation with France.
</P>
<P>
Xu also briefed Chirac on Shanghai's progress in the economy,
urban construction and environmental protection in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Chirac spoke highly of Shanghai's economic achievements, saying
that the city is one of the most vigorous ones in the world, and
that greater changes will take place in Shanghai in the 21st
century, the economic center of China.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today Chirac attended the opening ceremony of a
French hi-tech fair.
</P>
<P>
He said at the ceremony that this is the second time within two
years that France has held such a fair in Shanghai. Over 300 of
France's leading businesses are represented at the fair, which is
the largest one France has ever held abroad.
</P>
<P>
Chirac expressed the hope that the fair, covering the fields of
aviation, telecommunications, energy, chemicals, pharmaceuticals
and environmental protection, will become an important milestone
in the advance of the Franco-Chinese partnership into the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Although some French businesses have entered the Chinese
market, the scale of French investment in China does not match
the potential of French-Chinese ties, he said, adding that more
French enterprises s=hould come to China.
</P>
<P>
Chirac arrived here this morning from Beijing. 
