<HEADLINE> Iran Arrests Outlawed Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran said today its intelligence
service had arrested some members of an anti-government
organization called Mujaheddin Khalq Outfit (MKO) in
Khomeinishahr, some 900 kilometers west of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
However, Iran's official news agency did not specify how many
MKO members were actually arrested.
</P>
<P>
A director of the provincial intelligence department said, on
condition of anonymity, that the MKO members were arrested after
being identified in Khomeinishahr last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the MKO team had been engaged in
stirring up disturbance and disorder among the people of the
region.
</P>
<P>
The arrested elements were handed over to the judicial
officials of the province, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian authorities have tightened security across the
country as the 7th presidential elections, slated to be held on
May 23, are approaching.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the fourth parliament elections in 1992, the
MKO made a series of bombing attacks in the country and the
government reacted by staging an air raid on the MKO base inside
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The MKO led by Mass'oud Rajavi, who lives in Iraq at the
moment, has about 20,000 members in Iraq at present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970517.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Advances into Women's Basketball Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- South Korea advanced into the women's
basketball final after beating China 88-78 in a semi-final match at
the second East Asian Games here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
South Korea displayed a brilliant team-work in the game, edgeing
their Chinese rivals 88-78 after leading the halftime 45-35.
</P>
<P>
China, led by two national team players Liang Xin and Jiang Xu, had
a flying start in the match, leading the score 8-2, 10-5 in the first
five minutes.
</P>
<P>
However, under the pressure of the South Korean players, the
Chinese squad, with most members from junior team, did not maintain
ther pace and was lagged behind before the interval.
</P>
<P>
"We played to our best," said Liang Xin. "The South Korean team,
mainly from their national team, is much stronger than us."
</P>
<P>
Yoo Young Joo of South Korea had the game high score of 30 points,
Chung Eun Soon and Chun Joo Weon added 20 and 17 points for the
winners respectively.
</P>
<P>
Liang Xin and Jiang Xu were the only two players in the Chinese
team who had two-digit points. Liang Xin had 25 and Jiang Xu 23.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean team will meet Japan in the final which is slated
for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese team, with 27 points from Yuko Aizawa, defeated
Chinese Taipei 85-84 in another semi-final match.
</P>
<P>
After being lagged behind 44-49 in the first half, the Japanese
girls acceralted their attacking pace, beating their rivals from
Chinese Taipei 41-35.
</P>
<P>
Satomi Hirate and Taeko Oyama each had 17 points while Akemi
Okazato added 10 for the winners.
</P>
<P>
While in the men's basketball tournament, South Korea defeated
China 73-69, Kazakhstan beat Mongolia 85-62 and Japan outplayed Guam
88-70 in the last round robins.
</P>
<P>
The semi-final matches will take China against Chinese Taipei and
Kazakhstan vs South Korea on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
