<HEADLINE> Study Deng Xiaoping's Ideas on Science: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- A senior leader of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) urged here today that Deng Xiaoping's thought
on science and technology be studied by cadres and the general
public.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, was speaking at a seminar sponsored by the Chinese
Academy of Sciences. He said that Deng's thoughts on science are
an important component of his theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
In particular, his innovative statement that "science and
technology are the No.1 productive force" has greatly enriched the
Marxist theory in this regard, Wen said.
</P>
<P>
He said that people should use Deng's theory to observe,
analyze and solve problems, thus maintaining a correct orientation
for scientific and technological work.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Deng's thought should be used to solve problems
that are hindering the development of China's economy and
science, he added, citing problems in the sectors of agriculture,
energy and the environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
