<HEADLINE> Iran Welcomes Foreign Experts to Quake-Hit Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran said here today that it
welcomes foreign experts to inspect Khorasan's quake-hit areas and
study the recent tremor in east Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry was quoted by local radio as expressing
its gratitude to those countries that have provided humanitarian
relief aid to the quake victims in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that the international assistance
amounted to 3.3 million U.S. dollars, including 810,000 dollars
from the U.N. agencies.
</P>
<P>
A 7.1-magnitude killer earthquake hit Qaen and Birjand areas,
about 800 kilometers east of the Iranian capital of Tehran, last
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Iran's Natural Disaster Headquarters said that the quake has
left 1,567 people dead, several hundred injured while 15,000
houses were destroyed. 
