<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TVs, ACs Smuggling Costs 62m Dollars to Pak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's national exchequer is
losing about 2.5 billion rupees (about 62 million U.S. dollars)
per annum in revenues due to smuggling of television sets and air
conditioners.
</P>
<P>
According to a market survey, sales of at least 6 brands of
locally manufactured TVs and 4 brands of air conditioners have
gone down by 50 percent during the last couple of years.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that despite a guarantee of two to three years
to consumers in case of local products, consumers prefer to buy
smuggled items, which are often cheaper in price than the local
products.
</P>
<P>
According to the Pakistan Electronic Manufacturers Association,
0.5 million television sets of various brands are smuggled
annually into Pakistan, against a demand of 0.8 million television
sets per annum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
