<HEADLINE> South Koreans Take Two Judo Titltes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- South Korean judokas notched up two gold
medals from four categories on the seventh day of the second East
Asian Games here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Other two titles were split by China and Japan through Liu Chuang
and Nagai Kazue respectively.
</P>
<P>
Kwak Dae Sung of South Korea, who finished second at the Atlanta
Olympic Games last summer, defeated Japanese rival Nakamura Kenzo to
win the men's 71kg category.
</P>
<P>
Ba Teer of China finished third in the division.
</P>
<P>
Another title for the host country was from Kim Hyuk, who beat
Uchimura Naoya of Japan to take the men's 65kg category. Uuganba
Erdenebaatar of Mongolia and Lin Wen Tao of Chinese Taipei shared the
bronze medal in the event.
</P>
<P>
Liu Chuang, who finished fifth in Atlanta, took the second gold
medal for China from judo, beating Huang Ai Chun of Chinese Taipei in
the women's 56kg division.
</P>
<P>
Otsuka Masako of Japan and Park Mi Hee of South Korea finished
third.
</P>
<P>
The only other gold medal on the day went to Japanese judoka Nagai
Kazue, who beat Hyun Sook Hee of South Korea in the women's 52kg
category.
</P>
<P>
