<HEADLINE> Zairian Rebels Enter Kinshasa, Defense Minister Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Zairian rebels led by Laurent-Desire
Kabila have entered the capital and are near the center of the
city this morning, according to witnesses.
</P>
<P>
The streets of Kinshasa remained deserted this morning and no
sign of street fighting during the night was seen.
</P>
<P>
The shooting of automatic weapons was heard throughout this
morning from the international airport of Ndjili, 25 kilometers
north of Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
Zairian Defense Minister General Mahele Liyoko was killed by
soldiers of the elite Special Presidential Division (DSP), early
this morning in unclear circumstances.
</P>
<P>
The Zairian rebels have called for an unconditional surrender
of the government troops.
</P>
<P>
Some sources said that Liyoko was asking the soldiers to lay down
their arms and surrender to the rebels. The soldiers executed him
as a traitor outside the Tshatchi barracks where President Mobutu
Sese Seko stayed until his departure Friday.
</P>
<P>
The son of President Mobutu, Commander Mobutu Kungulu, is in the
Tshatchi camp of the DSP, whose commander, General Nzimbi, had fled
to Congo.
</P>
<P>
The French embassy denied that Mobutu Kungulu was seeking asylum
in the embassy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
