<HEADLINE> Bus Service Between Kampala, Goma Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 17 (xinhua) -- A transport firm called Horizon
Coaches has started operating direct services to Goma in eastern
Zaire from Uganda's capital, Kampala, local daily ''The New
Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
A source within the firm was quoted by the paper as saying
that this is to cater for the increasing number of travellers and
businessmen from the central African country.
</P>
<P>
the source preferring anonymity said, ''One bus is plying to
Goma though, but another will soon be allocated to supplement the
high demand.''
</P>
<P>
The bus made its maiden trip to Goma early this week, the
source said, adding that the 13-hour long journey takes
passengers from Kampala to Zaire's eastern town of Goma. 
</P>
</TEXT>
