<HEADLINE> Senior Official: Turkey Praises China's Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- A senior Turkish official has
commended China's policy on Hong Kong, saying that its return to
China will enhance new strength, provide new opportunities and
bring benefits for the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry Undersecretary Onur Oymen made
the remarks in an exclusive interview with Xinhua at his office
in Ankara later Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey maintains that the Chinese government will support Hong
Kong to "maintain its characteristics" and will ensure Hong Kong's
economic prosperity, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the concept of 'One China, Two Systems' will be
successful in China," said the undersecretary.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the belief that China will become one of the
most economically advanced countries in the world in the 21th
century.
</P>
<P>
Oymen pointed out that China has been implementing a very wise
economic policy in recent years and this policy has provided many
conveniences for developing the market economy, saying that for
this reason, Turkey is making efforts to develop its economic
ties with China.
</P>
<P>
So far, some Turkish firms have invested in China and Turkey
is trying to step up such investments in China in the future,
Oymen added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
