<HEADLINE> Turkey Respects China's Sovereignty: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Turkish official has
said that Turkey respects China's independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity at any time as China is Turkey's very
important and great friend.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua in Ankara late Friday,
Turkish Foreign Ministry Undersecretary Onur Oymen said that
Turkey and China are important states "at the two ends of Asia,"
both with a long history and rich experience. He added that the
close cooperation between the two countries "will be beneficial
not only to the whole Asia, but also to the whole world."
</P>
<P>
On the issue of resorting to violence, Oymen said "We will not
favor any organization or any people to use violence for whatever
purpose and no matter in China or in Turkey, in the Middle East
or in Europe" as "no political results" can be achieved through
resorting to violence.
</P>
<P>
"Any people can not change the border of a country through
violence," he added.
</P>
<P>
The undersecretary expressed his hope that the people of the
national minorities living in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region will become a bridge linking the friendship between
Turkey and China.
</P>
<P>
Oymen pointed out that Turkey and China should promote
exchange of high-level visits and cooperation in a bid to enhance
the existing bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
