<HEADLINE> Russian Olympic Champion Claims Men's 3-meter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Dimitry Santin, Russian Olympic
champion last year at Atlanta, won the men's 3-meter springboard
Friday at the Mexico international diving tournament in Juarez
City.
</P>
<P>
Santin beat other 11 finalists to seal the winner with a total
score of 661 points. His close opponent Lengyel Imre of Hungria
received 638 points for second place. Mexcio's Fernando Platas was
third at 631 points.
</P>
<P>
In the women's synchronized diving competition, Anna Lindberg
and Ienny Lingamfelter of the United States took the title at 269
points. Russians Julia Pakhalina and Olga Khristoforova was second
at 252 points with Americans Kim Stanfield and Dorls Glenn third
in 243 points.
</P>
<P>
The tournament, participated by more than 80 divers from 12
countries and regions, will conclude Saturday after men's and
women's 10-meter platform events. 
