cobalt from the slag dumps at Nkana in the province. The waste slags
are being transported to kabwe for processing into cobalt alloy.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba was delighted with the investment which has already
offered 200 jobs to the local peole. He said, "This is a positive
development to Kabwe expecially that many people lost jobs after the
closure of the Kabwe mine. Our people in kabwe need development and
my government welcomes any positive contribution to revitalize
Kabwe." 
