visiting French President Jacques Chirac and Chinese Vice-Premier
Wu Bangguo here today.
</P>
<P>
The CASC/Airbus Training and Support Center located near the
Capital Airport was jointly established by the China Aviation
Supplies Import &AMP; Export Corporation (CASC) and the Airbus
Industrie, a European company headquartered in France.
</P>
<P>
The center, with a total coverage of more than 14,300 square
meters and an investment of more than 100 million US dollars, was
jointly designed by the China Aeronautical Project and Design
Institute and the Laborie Company of France. It constitutes part
of the Airbus Industrie global training and support network.
</P>
<P>
President Chirac, who arrived in Beijing Thursday on a state
visit to China, left here for China's largest metropolis of
Shanghai after the inauguration ceremony this morning.
</P>
<P>
On the president's first day of visit, the two governments
reached a series of agreements or letters of intent including a
framework accord on the purchase of 30 Airbus planes by the
CASC.  
