<HEADLINE> Real Estate Builds On Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's property market has seen
another month of recovery after six months of being in the
doldrums, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The slow build-up from decline started in March, figures from
China Real Estate Index system indicate.
</P>
<P>
But real estate observers said several more months are needed
to testify if another round of development in the property market
in the capital city is on the cards after a slack performance that
started in 1993.
</P>
<P>
A report from officials at the index said that Beijing's real
estate price index edged up 1.5 points to 1,092.5 in April, with
office buildings leading the trend, boasting a seven-point
increase.
</P>
<P>
Prices for housing are stable, up only half of one point, while
prices for commercial space and warehousing showed no fluctuations
in April.
</P>
<P>
The indexing system was launched to monitor market changes
nationwide. It bases its calculations on property prices,
reckoning average property prices in November 1994 in Beijing as
1,0000 points.
</P>
<P>
Deng Qing, director at the index's system office, said several
favorable factors, such as two interest-rate cuts and an economic
rearrangement last year, are having an impact on the realty
market, which helped property prices to maintain growth over the
past two months.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
