co-operation from one overwhelmingly dependent on aid to a
mutually beneficial one sustained by investments and trade," said
President Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
He said Tanzania is currently putting a lot of emphasis on
encouraging and facilitating the individual and institutional
will to develop.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa said that Tanzania is trying to get a grip on policy
initiatives for broad-based development in which donor
particcipation is supplementary rather than a substitute for the
people's own efforts.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa thanked Finland for its great contribution to Tanzania's
socio-economic development for the past 30 years and called for
revitalised co-operation.
</P>
<P>
"But time has now come for us to review this co-operation and
revitalise it in conformity with the changed circumstances in our
two countries and in the world," said Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
On regional politics, President Mkapa called on the
international community to fulfil its obligations towards
refugees and displaced people, saying that countries hosting
refugees like Tanzania should be supported to bear the burden.
</P>
<P>
President Ahtisaari said that the 16 prominent Finnish
businessmen accompanying him intended to strengthen trade and
economic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He commended Tanzania for her selfless efforts in looking
after a large number of refugees from Burundi, Zaire and Rwanda,
adding that Finland supported Mwalimu Juliu Nyerere's mediation
role in the Burundi crisis.
</P>
<P>
President Ahtisaari arrived here last evening for a three-day
official visit to Tanzania. 
