</P>
<P>
Chand, who returned here today from the summit of the South
Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) via India, told
reporters at the airport that one of the important achievements of
the 9th SAARC summit was the consensus on promoting sub-regional
cooperation within the SAARC framework.
</P>
<P>
Some misunderstanding arising over the sub-regional cooperation
concept has now been cleared up by the summit in Male, the prime
minister said.
</P>
<P>
A declaration adopted at the SAARC summit allows three or more
member countries to cooperate on specific projects under the
principle of mutual benefits.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Foreign Minister Prakash Chandra Lohani last December
proposed the idea of sub-regional cooperation in South Asia, or
the Growth Quadrangle including Nepal, Bangladesh, Bhutan and
India, with a view to promoting multi-lateral joint development
efforts in areas like water resources, transportation,
communications and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The concept of sub-region cooperation earlier had drawn fears
among other SAARC members about its possible impact on the
seven-member regional grouping, which was formed in 1985. Other
SAARC members are the Maldives, Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Lohani, who returned here earlier on Friday, said that the
sub-region cooperation now could embark on by identifying specific
projects.
</P>
<P>
Nepal was entrusted last month coordinator in the first-phase
of the four-nation sub-regional cooperation, which will enlist
projects to be studied in detail later on.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
