<HEADLINE> Shuttle Atlantis Docks with Russian Space Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. space shuttle Atlantis
docked late tonight with Russian space station, the Mir, ferrying
repair equipment, a replacement oxygen generator and a new crew
member to the outpost.
</P>
<P>
Under the guide of Commander Charles Precourt, Atlantis had a
gentle rendezvous with the Mir at about 10:38 p.m. (17:38
p.m. GMT)in the sixth of nine planned shuttle-Mir dockings to
prepare for a future international space station.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule of the National Aeronautics and Space
Administration (NASA), the astronauts will open the hatch between
the two spacecraft two hours later. Then Michael Foale will switch
his place with another American astronaut Jerry Linenger, who has
been living there since mid-January. 
</P>
