<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shuttle Atlantis Docks with Russian Space Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. space shuttle Atlantis
docked late tonight with Russian space station, the Mir, ferrying
repair equipment, a replacement oxygen generator and a new crew
member to the outpost.
</P>
<P>
Under the guide of Commander Charles Precourt, Atlantis had a
gentle rendezvous with the Mir at about 10:33 p.m. (02:33 GMT)in
the sixth of nine planned shuttle-Mir dockings to prepare for a
future international space station.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule of the National Aeronautics and Space
Administration (NASA), the astronauts will open the hatch between
the two spacecraft two hours later. Then Michael Foale will switch
his place with another American astronaut Jerry Linenger, who has
been living there since mid-January.
</P>
<P>
Along with picking up Linenger and dropping off Foale,
Atlantis will deliver more than three tons of water, food, a
new oxygen generator and other science equipment and hardware.
</P>
<P>
Unloading all the goods will probably take five days.
</P>
<P>
Atlantis, the 84th of all American shuttle flights and the
fourth of the year, is expected to land at Kennedy Space Center,
Florida, on May 24.
</P>
<P>
Before the shuttle's launch early Thursday, Dr. Foale told
reporters that he was looking forward to spending the next four
months aboard the Russian complex despite the possibility of
trouble on the 120-ton Mir station.
</P>
<P>
"The station has been up there a long time and there's a lot
of work to do to keep repairing it, maintaining it....I actually
look forward sometimes to these off-nominal situations when things
don't quite go per plan," Foale said.
</P>
<P>
A fire broke out on board in February, and the main oxygen
generator shut down in March. A cooling equipment is leaking and
the carbon dioxide removing system has been a constant headache.
</P>
<P>
Although its predicted life is only five years, the Mir has
circled the Earth more than 64,000 times since its launching in
1986. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970517.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Insists on Consolidating Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELO HORIZONTE, Brazil, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Foreign
Relations Minister Luiz Felipe Lampreia insisted today on the
consolidation of the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) before the
creation of the Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA).
</P>
<P>
He made clear his stance at the 3rd Meeting of Commerce
Ministers of the Americas held here from Thursday to Friday to
discuss the establishment of FTAA, due in the year 2005, by all
the American countries except Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, the biggest South American trade bloc formed by
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, is a success with a gross
domestic product surpassing 1.1 trillion U.S. dollars and a 200
million people market, Lampreia said, stressing the strengthening
and consolidation of it is good for FTAA.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, which faces an increasing trade deficit, insisted on
three basic principles on the establishment of FTAA: the
indissolubility of Mercosur, talks split into stages with tariff
cuts left until last, and a balance between the commitments FTAA
could offer and the profits obtained by its members.
</P>
<P>
Lampreia said eliminating trade barriers among the continent is a
first step to the negotiation of customs tariffs reduction,
while the United States wants everything from tariff cuts to
subsidies to be discussed at the same time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970517.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysians Urged to Seek Opportunities in Info-Tech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad has called on all the Malaysians to open up their minds to
the wide-ranging possibilities and opportunities available in
information and multimedia technology development.
</P>
<P>
He made the call today when he officiated the ground-breaking
ceremony and the launching of Cyberjaya in Sepang near here, which
is Malaysia's first smart city located in the Multimedia Super
Corridor (MSC), marking the start of the physical construction of
the MSC.
</P>
<P>
Cyberjaya covering an area of 2,800 hectares is the nucleus of
the MSC, the world's leading intelligent city comparable to the
Silicon Valley in California, U.S. and other similar cities.
</P>
<P>
Next to Cyberjaya is Putrajaya, the federal government's new
administrative center on a 7,000-hectare site. Cyberjaya and
Putrajaya will be separated by a highway known as Route 2020.
</P>
<P>
The MSC, a 15 kilometer by 50 kilometer zone specially for
hi-tech development, is stretching southward from the Kuala
Lumpur city center and is designed to serve as a regional launch
site for companies developing or using advanced multimedia
technologies.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said information and multimedia technology should
never be an end in itself. Effectively used, it will act as a
valuable input, and in many cases, a catalyst for many other
industries.
</P>
<P>
He said "advances in multimedia technology will lead to new
applications, spurring the growth of trade and commerce, as well
as the growth of productivity and efficiency in all the sectors."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said although the MSC, particularly Cyberjaya, was
intended to facilitate the country's transition to an information
age multimedia economy, it did not mean that other industries
would take a backseat.
</P>
<P>
There would be numerous opportunities and spin-off benefits in
Cyberjaya, the impact of which would be felt for many generations
ahead, he said adding for example, there would be plenty of rooms
to provide content and value-added services although the main
pipeline would be the multimedia services.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to take this opportunity to call upon local
companies to look into strategic alliances and collaboration with
global companies to explore this wide area of content development,
especially to meet the need of the Asia Pacific communities, whose
cultural and social value system may defer from those of the
West," he said.
</P>
<P>
Seven specific sites have already been identified for the
location of some of the pioneering projects in the Flagship Zone
which is the hub of Cyberjaya and a total of 39 companies, both
local and foreign, have already committed to locating their
operations in Cyberjaya.
</P>
<P>
According to Mahathir, by late 1998, phase one, comprising a
750-hectare development area, would be completed while the
remaining area would be developed in stages up to the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
He said based on the high level of interest generated and
positive feedback received over the past few months, his
government was confident that many other companies would soon
follow the lead.
</P>
<P>
Since the launch of MSC last year, Mahathir visited the U.S.
and Japan to personally explain Malaysia's plan to build the
corridor and invite world leading hi-tech companies to invest in
the MSC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
