<HEADLINE> Cambodia to Combat Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia will take severe
measures to combat the transnational drug trafficking, media
reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Drug trafficking in Cambodia became rampant recently, the media
said, with criminal rings from Hong Kong and elsewhere using the
country as a transit for drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Police recently found that a drug trafficking group from Japan
has also entered Cambodia. It is most alarming that the group not
only trades in drugs, but also in children.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian government has ordered governmental departments
to give full support to the fight against transnational criminal
groups and keep the nation in good order. 
