<HEADLINE> Peru Requests to be Admitted to Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELO HORIZONTE, Brazil, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Peruvian
government today requested to be admitted into the Southern Common
Market (Mercosur), the biggest South American trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
The request was put forward by Commerce Minister Gustavo
Caillaux Zazzali to a meeting of Commerce Ministers of the
Americas here to discuss the establishment of the Free Trade Area
of Americas (FTAA) in the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
Consideration of Peru's partial inclusion in Mercosur will be
resumed June 10 in Montevideo, Uruguay, according to the Brazilian
Foreign Relations Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Peru withdrew on April 11 from the Andean Group to negotiate
its admission to Mercosur formed by Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay
and Uruguay. 
