<HEADLINE> Chinese, Argentine Firms Sign Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Argentine
enterprises signed here today a number of agreements to promote
economic and commercial links between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The documents, signed during Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing's
visit here, include one on 30-million U.S. dollars credit from the
Import and Export Bank of China to three Argentine banks and one
on road building machinery between the Chinese Import and Export
Corporation of Engineering and Agriculture Machinery and the
Argentine province of Misiones.
</P>
<P>
Letters of intention on the construction of a soybean oil
plant, a color TV plant and other projects were also signed.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived here on Thursday, said at the signing ceremony
that his Argentina visit was aimed at promoting economic and
commercial links on the basis of the excellent political relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Argentine entrepreneurs on China's current economic
situation and achievements since the country began to implement
the policy of reform and opening up in 1979.
</P>
<P>
He said that on the eve of the new millennium, the Chinese
government was willing to deepen relations with Argentina and
other Latin American countries.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Economics Minister Roque Fernandez hailed China's
economic successes over recent years, adding Argentina was also
going through a process of reform and the two countries could
exchange experiences to achieve better economic and social
developments.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice prime, who heads a Chinese business and trade
delegation, will wind up his Latin American tour Sunday which has
already taken him to Brazil, Cuba, Colombia and Chile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
