<HEADLINE> Poland, Slovakia to Develop Border Water Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Poland and Hungary have entered an
intergovernmental agreement on joint development of border water
conservancy projects, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed by Polish Foreign Minister Dariusz Rosati
and his Slovak counterpart, Pavol Hamzik, during the latter's
two-day official visit here Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Hamzik also held talks with President
Aleksander Kwasniewski and Rosati on bilateral relations, European
security and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization's eastward
expansion. 
</P>
