<HEADLINE> Brazil Demands Registration of Foreign Wines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- All foreign wines sold in Brazil
will be registered in the Agriculture Ministry of the country, an
official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation stipulates that foreign wine producers
should also register their products and establishments in the
Agriculture and Livestock Defense Secretariat of the same ministry.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the rule is to know better the origin of the
wine consumed in the South American country.
</P>
<P>
Some countries are exempted since they signed agreements with
Brazil on the matter.
</P>
<P>
Alemania, the main exporter of wine to Brazil, is considering
signing such an agreement with Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
