<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Border Trade Still Strong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Border trade between Russia and
Heilongjiang province in northeast China was worth 220 million US
dollars in the January to April period, up 133 percent from the
same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Exports were worth 49.46 million US dollars in the first four
months of 1997, twice the amount of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Light industrial exports of garments and food accounted for
32.5 percent of the total. Exports of local products and grain
also increased, and plums accounted for 39 percent of the imports.
</P>
<P>
The province sent 3,546 laborers to Russia, twice the amount of
the same period in 1996. Heilongjiang has also signed 67
cooperative projects, 24 percent higher than the same period of
1996.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang has a 3,045-km border with Russia and the largest
number of ports open to Russia. Thanks to its long border, it had
eight billion US dollars worth of imports and exports from 1987 to
1996, accounting for two-thirds of the total China-Russia trade.
</P>
</TEXT>
