<HEADLINE> East China Province Trying To Clean Up Polluted Huai River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Anhui Province in east China is
increasing efforts to see that all polluters along the Huaihe,
one of the major rivers in the province and one of the most
polluted, meet discharge standards by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The State Council, China's cabinet, has called for all
polluters along the river valley to meet the standards and the
provincial government has made arrangements for dealing with the
pollution.
</P>
<P>
A waste treatment project for the Anhui Paper Mill has begun
with a pollution-treatment fund of 12 million yuan (about 1.4
million US dollars). The project is expected to be completed by
October.
</P>
<P>
The Bengbu Ethyl factory has spent 80 million yuan on a
technological renovation project, and the factory now stops liquid
ethyl from polluting the Huaihe.
</P>
<P>
Provincial leaders have shown a determination to make all
polluters meet the discharge standards by the end of the year.
</P>
</TEXT>
