<HEADLINE> Courier Falls, Ivanisevic Wins in Quarter-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 16 (Xinhua) -- American Jim Courier said good-by to
the Italian Open Friday night when he was defeated by Chile's
Marcelo Rios, while Croatian Goran Ivanisevic stopped Australian
Scotte Draper to enter the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Seventh-seeded Rios beat Courier 6-3, 3-6, 7-6 (7/4) and now
faces Spain's Alberto Berasategui in Saturday's semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Courier, who won here in 1992 and 1993, had few regrets about
his match, despite the missed chances.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui beat Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner 7-5, 7-5 in the
night match to book his date with Rios.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic scored a 6-4, 6-4 win over Draper, who had knocked
out defending champion Thomas Muster, in the quarterfinals. Now
The croatian meets Spaniard Alex Corretja in the other semi-final.
</P>
<P>
Corretja rallied from a set down to beat Morocco's Karim Alami
4-6, 7-5, 6-3, with decisive moment coming in the 12th game of
the second set.  
