<HEADLINE> Holiday Wins IBF Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Phillip Holiday retained his
International Boxing Federation (IBF) world lightweight title on a
split decision over Pete Taliaferro at the Carousel casino resort
north of Pretoria Friday night.
</P>
<P>
South African Holiday, making the sixth defense of the
champion, survived a second-round knockdown but never really
impressed, according to a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
It said his performance did little to underwrite his rating by
Ring Magazine as the top lightweight in the world.
</P>
<P>
The challenger Taliaferro from America took the early rounds,
which swayed Puerto Rican judge Ceasar Ramos to score the fight
115-111 in his favour.
</P>
<P>
The other two judges scored it 115-111 for Holiday. 
</P>
