<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Companies Seek Cleaner Image </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of factories and workshops
in Beijing have introduced pollution control and energy saving
measures, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
And a top official has revealed that many of the ecology
schemes have cost little to implement such measures, but have had
a major impact on the environment in China's capital city.
</P>
<P>
So far 50 workshops of 39 enterprises in Beijing have carried
out cleaner production measures. They rationally use resources
and energy, and minimize the production of waste.
</P>
<P>
The practice, introduced over the past four years, proves that
while the enterprises have reduced waste discharge by a large
amount during the process of carrying out cleaner production,
their production cost have also been reduced with more benefits
for the environment.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Xia, an official at Beijing's Environmental Protection
Bureau, disclosed at a press conference that 60 percent of the
schemes for cleaner production measures used in the 50 shops cost
little, but would lead to a 1.84-million-ton reduction in waste
water discharge, and save 366,000 tons of fresh water, reaping
economic benefits of 66.77 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said the active promotion of cleaner production, which
emphasizes pollution prevention during production process, is an
important measure against industrial pollution on the way towards
sustainable development in the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Many enterprises both at home and abroad have taken cleaner
production as an important part of their development strategy,
according to Cheng.
</P>
<P>
She said that both the enterprises which are lagging behind in
technology and equipment, or short of funds, and those which
claim advanced management and production methods and techniques,
have benefited from the implementation of cleaner production in
the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
