<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Police Seize 199 kg of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican anti-drug agents
seized 199 kilograms of cocaine and detained 14 suspects,
including an alleged drug trafficking kingpin, authorities said
today.
</P>
<P>
Agents raided a van traveling to Nicaragua Thursday and seized
the drug. In another raid, they arrested alleged drug chieftain
William Cubillo and eight other suspects near the border with
Panama.
</P>
<P>
Police officers rounded up two more suspects in a mechanical
shop in Heredia in central Costa Rica, where the drug was
allegedly packaged.
</P>
<P>
Three other arrests were made in San Jose and Liberia, a town
near the border with Nicaragua, police said.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica is used by international drug traffickers as a major
transit for drugs to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican police seized 370 kilograms of cocaine aboard a
truck traveling to Guatemala a month ago. 
</P>
